question_text: What is the difference between val and const val?
correct_answer: val: runtime constant; const val: compile-time constant (top-level or in object).

question_text: What is the difference between lateinit and lazy?
correct_answer: lateinit: mutable

question_text: What is the difference between var and mutableList?
correct_answer: var: variable reference can change; mutableList: content can change but reference may be val.

question_text: What is the difference between List and Array?
correct_answer: List: interface

question_text: What is the difference between == and ===?
correct_answer: ==: structural equality (equals()); ===: referential equality (same object).

question_text: What is the difference between fun and val with lambda?
correct_answer: fun: function declaration; val with lambda: function stored in variable.

question_text: What is the difference between inline and noinline?
correct_answer: inline: function body inserted at call site; noinline: prevents inlining of specific lambda parameters.

question_text: What is the difference between crossinline and noinline?
correct_answer: crossinline: lambda cannot use non-local returns; noinline: prevents inlining entirely.

question_text: What is the difference between let and also?
correct_answer: let: returns lambda result; also: returns context object.

question_text: What is the difference between apply and run?
correct_answer: apply: returns context object; run: returns lambda result.

question_text: What is the difference between with and run?
correct_answer: with: non-extension function; run: extension or non-extension.

question_text: What is the difference between takeIf and takeUnless?
correct_answer: takeIf: returns object if condition true; takeUnless: returns object if condition false.

question_text: What is the difference between class and data class?
correct_answer: class: regular class; data class: automatically generates equals()

question_text: What is the difference between object and companion object?
correct_answer: object: singleton instance; companion object: singleton tied to containing class.

question_text: What is the difference between abstract class and interface?
correct_answer: abstract class: can have state
explanation: constructors; interface: can have default implementations (no state).

question_text: What is the difference between open class and sealed class?
correct_answer: open class: can be inherited; sealed class: restricted inheritance (subclasses in same file).

question_text: What is the difference between inner class and nested class?
correct_answer: inner class: has reference to outer class; nested class: static

question_text: What is the difference between by lazy and Delegates.observable?
correct_answer: by lazy: lazy initialization; Delegates.observable: property change observation.

question_text: What is the difference between by Delegates.vetoable and observable?
correct_answer: vetoable: can veto changes; observable: only observes changes.

question_text: What is the difference between ?. and ?:?
correct_answer: ?.: safe call operator; ?:: Elvis operator (default value).

question_text: What is the difference between !! and ?.
correct_answer: !!: non-null assertion (throws NPE); ?.: safe call (returns null).

question_text: What is the difference between launch and async?
correct_answer: launch: fire-and-forget; async: returns Deferred result.

question_text: What is the difference between Dispatchers.IO and Dispatchers.Default?
correct_answer: IO: optimized for I/O operations; Default: CPU-intensive work.

question_text: What is the difference between withContext and async/await?
correct_answer: withContext: switches context and returns result; async/await: concurrent decomposition.

question_text: What is the difference between CoroutineScope and GlobalScope?
correct_answer: CoroutineScope: structured concurrency; GlobalScope: application lifetime.

question_text: What is the difference between Job and Deferred?
correct_answer: Job: represents cancellable work; Deferred: Job with result.

question_text: What is the difference between map and flatMap?
correct_answer: map: transforms each element; flatMap: transforms and flattens.

question_text: What is the difference between filter and filterNot?
correct_answer: filter: keeps matching elements; filterNot: keeps non-matching elements.

question_text: What is the difference between first and firstOrNull?
correct_answer: first: throws if empty; firstOrNull: returns null if empty.

question_text: What is the difference between sequence and list?
correct_answer: sequence: lazy evaluation; list: eager evaluation.

question_text: What is the difference between associateBy and groupBy?
correct_answer: associateBy: last value per key; groupBy: all values per key.

question_text: What is the difference between Any and Unit?
correct_answer: Any: root superclass; Unit: equivalent to void (single value).

question_text: What is the difference between Nothing and Unit?
correct_answer: Nothing: no values (never returns); Unit: single value (void).

question_text: What is the difference between reified and inline?
correct_answer: reified: preserves type at runtime; inline: required for reified type parameters.

question_text: What is the difference between when and switch?
correct_answer: can match types

question_text: What is the difference between require and check?
correct_answer: require: validates arguments (IllegalArgumentException); check: validates state (IllegalStateException).

question_text: What is the difference between assert and require?
correct_answer: assert: for debugging (enabled with -ea); require: for public API validation.

question_text: What is the difference between @JvmStatic and companion object?
correct_answer: @JvmStatic: exposes as static method to Java; companion object: Kotlin's way of static members.

question_text: What is the difference between @JvmOverloads and default parameters?
correct_answer: @JvmOverloads: generates overloads for Java; default parameters: Kotlin feature.

question_text: What is the difference between fold and reduce?
correct_answer: fold: takes initial value; reduce: uses first element as initial.

question_text: What is the difference between map and forEach?
correct_answer: map: returns new collection; forEach: performs side effects.

question_text: What is the difference between extension function and member function?
correct_answer: extension function: defined outside class; member function: defined inside class (higher priority).

question_text: What is the difference between @JvmField and lateinit?
correct_answer: @JvmField: exposes property as Java field; lateinit: deferred initialization.

question_text: What is the difference between builder pattern and apply scope function?
correct_answer: builder pattern: traditional pattern; apply: simpler alternative for configuration.

question_text: What is the difference between MutableList and List?
correct_answer: MutableList: can modify elements; List: read-only interface.

question_text: What is the difference between Set and MutableSet?
correct_answer: Set: immutable unique collection; MutableSet: modifiable unique collection.

question_text: What is the difference between Map and MutableMap?
correct_answer: Map: read-only key-value pairs; MutableMap: modifiable key-value pairs.

question_text: What is the difference between IntArray and Array<Int>?
correct_answer: IntArray: primitive int array (better performance); Array<Int>: boxed Integer array.

question_text: What is the difference between toList and toMutableList?
correct_answer: toList: returns read-only list; toMutableList: returns modifiable copy.

question_text: What is the difference between asSequence and toList?
correct_answer: asSequence: converts to lazy sequence; toList: creates eager list.

question_text: What is the difference between partition and filter?
correct_answer: partition: splits into two collections; filter: keeps matching elements.

question_text: What is the difference between zip and zipWithNext?
correct_answer: zip: pairs elements from two collections; zipWithNext: pairs adjacent elements.

question_text: What is the difference between chunked and windowed?
correct_answer: chunked: splits into chunks; windowed: sliding windows with optional step.

question_text: What is the difference between sorted and sortedBy?
correct_answer: sorted: natural order; sortedBy: custom order using selector function.

question_text: What is the difference between distinct and distinctBy?
correct_answer: distinct: removes duplicates; distinctBy: removes duplicates based on selector.

question_text: What is the difference between sum and sumOf?
correct_answer: sum: for numeric collections; sumOf: calculates sum of transformed values.

question_text: What is the difference between min and minBy?
correct_answer: min: minimum value; minBy: minimum based on selector.

question_text: What is the difference between max and maxBy?
correct_answer: max: maximum value; maxBy: maximum based on selector.

question_text: What is the difference between average and sum?
correct_answer: average: mean value; sum: total sum.

question_text: What is the difference between count and size?
correct_answer: count: can have predicate; size: always total elements.

question_text: What is the difference between any and all?
correct_answer: any: true if any element matches; all: true if all elements match.

question_text: What is the difference between none and any?
correct_answer: none: true if no elements match; any: true if any element matches.

question_text: What is the difference between find and firstOrNull?
correct_answer: find: alias for firstOrNull with predicate; firstOrNull: can be without predicate.

question_text: What is the difference between single and singleOrNull?
correct_answer: single: expects exactly one element; singleOrNull: returns null if not exactly one.

question_text: What is the difference between elementAt and get?
correct_answer: elementAt: throws IndexOutOfBoundsException; get: same but shorter syntax [].

question_text: What is the difference between elementAtOrElse and elementAtOrNull?
correct_answer: elementAtOrElse: provides default value; elementAtOrNull: returns null.

question_text: What is the difference between slice and take?
correct_answer: slice: takes indices or range; take: first n elements.

question_text: What is the difference between drop and filterNot?
correct_answer: drop: removes first n elements; filterNot: removes matching elements.

question_text: What is the difference between takeWhile and filter?
correct_answer: takeWhile: takes while predicate true; filter: takes all matching.

question_text: What is the difference between dropWhile and filterNot?
correct_answer: dropWhile: drops while predicate true; filterNot: drops all matching.

question_text: What is the difference between reversed and asReversed?
correct_answer: reversed: creates new reversed collection; asReversed: view (changes reflect original).

question_text: What is the difference between shuffled and shuffle?
correct_answer: shuffled: returns new shuffled collection; shuffle: shuffles in-place (mutable).

question_text: What is the difference between joinToString and joinTo?
correct_answer: joinToString: returns string; joinTo: appends to existing Appendable.

question_text: What is the difference between plus and add?
correct_answer: plus: operator +
explanation: returns new collection; add: mutable operation

question_text: What is the difference between minus and remove?
correct_answer: minus: operator -
explanation: returns new collection; remove: mutable operation

question_text: What is the difference between contains and in operator?
correct_answer: contains: method; in: operator (calls contains).

question_text: What is the difference between isEmpty and isNotEmpty?
correct_answer: isEmpty: true if empty; isNotEmpty: true if not empty.

question_text: What is the difference between isNullOrEmpty and isEmpty?
correct_answer: isNullOrEmpty: true if null or empty; isEmpty: assumes not null.

question_text: What is the difference between mutableListOf and listOf?
correct_answer: mutableListOf: creates mutable list; listOf: creates read-only list.

question_text: What is the difference between mutableSetOf and setOf?
correct_answer: mutableSetOf: creates mutable set; setOf: creates read-only set.

question_text: What is the difference between mutableMapOf and mapOf?
correct_answer: mutableMapOf: creates mutable map; mapOf: creates read-only map.

question_text: What is the difference between arrayOf and intArrayOf?
correct_answer: arrayOf: generic array; intArrayOf: primitive int array.

question_text: What is the difference between emptyList and listOf()
correct_answer: emptyList: singleton empty list; listOf(): creates new list (empty or with elements).

question_text: What is the difference between List and ArrayList?
correct_answer: List: interface; ArrayList: concrete implementation.

question_text: What is the difference between HashSet and LinkedHashSet?
correct_answer: HashSet: unordered; LinkedHashSet: maintains insertion order.

question_text: What is the difference between HashMap and LinkedHashMap?
correct_answer: HashMap: unordered; LinkedHashMap: maintains insertion order.

question_text: What is the difference between toTypedArray and toArray?
correct_answer: toTypedArray: Kotlin function; toArray: Java interop function.

question_text: What is the difference between asList and toList?
correct_answer: asList: view (changes reflect array); toList: copy.

question_text: What is the difference between associate and associateBy?
correct_answer: associate: creates map from pairs; associateBy: creates map from collection elements.

question_text: What is the difference between associateWith and associateBy?
correct_answer: associateWith: values from elements
explanation: keys from transform; associateBy: keys from elements

question_text: What is the difference between toMap and associateTo?
correct_answer: toMap: creates new map; associateTo: accumulates to existing map.

question_text: What is the difference between fold and foldIndexed?
correct_answer: fold: accumulates without index; foldIndexed: includes index in accumulator.

question_text: What is the difference between reduce and reduceIndexed?
correct_answer: reduce: without index; reduceIndexed: includes index in operation.

question_text: What is the difference between runningFold and fold?
correct_answer: runningFold: returns list of intermediate results; fold: returns final result.

question_text: What is the difference between runningReduce and reduce?
correct_answer: runningReduce: returns list of intermediate results; reduce: returns final result.

question_text: What is the difference between scan and runningFold?
correct_answer: scan: alias for runningFold; runningFold: newer name.

question_text: What is the difference between flatten and flatMap?
correct_answer: flatten: flattens nested collection; flatMap: maps then flattens.

question_text: What is the difference between unzip and partition?
correct_answer: unzip: splits list of pairs into two lists; partition: splits based on predicate.

question_text: What is the difference between windowed and sliding window?
correct_answer: windowed: Kotlin function; sliding window: conceptual term.

question_text: What is the difference between onEach and forEach?
correct_answer: onEach: returns collection; forEach: returns Unit.

question_text: What is the difference between withIndex and forEachIndexed?
correct_answer: withIndex: returns iterable of IndexedValue; forEachIndexed: performs action with index.

question_text: What is the difference between indices and 0..size-1?
correct_answer: indices: IntRange property; 0..size-1: manual range.

question_text: What is the difference between lastIndex and size-1?
correct_answer: lastIndex: property; size-1: calculation.

question_text: What is the difference between getOrElse and getOrNull?
correct_answer: getOrElse: provides default value; getOrNull: returns null.

question_text: What is the difference between getValue and get?
correct_answer: getValue: used by property delegation; get: standard access.

question_text: What is the difference between component1 and first?
correct_answer: component1: for destructuring; first: method access.

question_text: What is the difference between iterator and for loop?
correct_answer: iterator: returns Iterator object; for loop: uses iterator internally.

question_text: What is the difference between ListIterator and Iterator?
correct_answer: ListIterator: bidirectional; Iterator: forward only.

question_text: What is the difference between subList and slice?
correct_answer: subList: view (changes reflect original); slice: copy.

question_text: What is the difference between retainAll and removeAll?
correct_answer: retainAll: keeps only specified elements; removeAll: removes specified elements.

question_text: What is the difference between clear and removeAll?
correct_answer: clear: removes all elements; removeAll: removes matching elements.
